00:04:08:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:08:020000.Dialogue: Let me explain what we're doing here. Um, in 1969, the astronauts on Apollo 11 positioned reflectors on the surface of the moon, and we're going to shoot a laser off one of them and let the light bounce back into this photomultiplier.

00:04:20:170000.Speaker: Zack

00:04:31:010000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:04:49:080000.Speaker: Leonard

00:04:56:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:56:010000.Dialogue: Now, we'll be able to see the beam when it leaves, but it won't be strong enough when it comes back to be seen by the naked eye.

00:05:06:230000.Speaker: Leonard

00:05:47:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:47:020000.Dialogue: LEONARD: Yeah, but, uh, think about what this represents. The fact that we can do this is the only way of definitively proving that there are man-made objects on the moon, put there by a member of a species that only 60 years before had just invented the airplane.

00:06:05:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:10:54:010000.Dialogue: Okay, I'll walk down with you. So, last night was fun, huh?

00:10:57:170000.Dialogue: Yeah, it must have been. I just threw up in my closet.

00:11:02:130000.Dialogue: Bummer. Anyway, I was thinking tonight maybe we could catch a movie.

00:11:06:170000.Dialogue: Oh, yeah, tonight's not great for me.

00:11:08:140000.Dialogue: Doesn't have to be tonight. I'm free pretty much always.

00:11:12:090000.Dialogue: Leonard, last night was a mistake.

00:11:15:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:15:060000.Dialogue: When you say "mistake," do you mean a fortunate mistake, like the discovery of penicillin?

00:11:21:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:21:080000.Dialogue: Look, I'm sorry. I was drunk, I was lonely, I hated Zack. Can we just forget it ever happened?

00:11:27:080000.Dialogue: No, it's pretty well imprinted on my brain. Especially the whole rodeo thing.

00:11:34:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:34:160000.Dialogue: So, that's it? Wham, bam, thank you, Leonard?

00:11:37:140000.Dialogue: Look, I said I'm sorry. Can't you please let it go?

00:12:27:230000.Dialogue: Leonard, you gotta see this. We found a match for Sheldon.

00:12:38:090000.Dialogue: Do you know what he's talking about?

00:12:39:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:39:190000.Dialogue: Nope. Why don't you ask him?

00:12:41:000000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:41:000000.Dialogue: Leonard, what are you talking about?

00:12:42:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:42:040000.Dialogue: I don't want to talk about it.

00:12:45:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:45:170000.Dialogue: Whatever. Right now, Dr. Sheldon Cooper has to send an e-mail to his perfect match. "Greetings, fellow life-form..."

00:12:57:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:57:200000.Dialogue: If she can do it, I can do it. If she can do it, I can do it. If she can do it, I can do it. I can't do it.

00:13:12:100000.Speaker: Leslie
00:13:12:100000.Dialogue: Leonard Hofstadter. What're you doing here?

00:13:14:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:14:100000.Dialogue: Uh, I know! It's been a while!

00:13:18:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:18:030000.Dialogue: Right. Right. So how you doing?

00:13:25:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:25:100000.Dialogue: Uh, not bad. You remember when we used to have sex and you said that it didn't mean anything, it was just for fun?

00:13:33:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:33:150000.Dialogue: You, uh, want to do that again?

00:13:40:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:40:150000.Dialogue: She didn't dump me. We were just in different places in the relationship.

00:13:45:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:45:140000.Dialogue: Um... anyway, apparently, it's okay to go back to people you're no longer seeing and have recreational sex with them.

00:14:09:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:09:190000.Dialogue: Uh-oh. She wants to meet us.

00:14:15:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:15:120000.Dialogue: Yes, but him doesn't even know about her.

00:14:17:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:17:210000.Dialogue: Well, him about to find out about her.

00:14:23:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:23:060000.Dialogue: Who's going to tell whom about what?

00:14:28:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:28:010000.Dialogue: Your surprise confuses me. I live here.

00:14:32:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:32:220000.Dialogue: Right. So, listen, what are you doing tomorrow afternoon?

00:14:45:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:45:120000.Dialogue: It's a time of day I invented. It better defines the ambiguous period between afternoon and evening: preevning.

00:14:53:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:53:070000.Dialogue: I'm fairly certain it will catch on as it fills a desperate need.

00:14:56:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:56:210000.Dialogue: Right, okay. What are you doing tomorrow preevning?

00:15:00:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:00:180000.Dialogue: Well, tomorrow's Saturday. Saturday night is laundry night. So I'll be spending the preevning pre-sorting and pre-soaking.

00:15:08:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:08:160000.Dialogue: Okay, what if I were to tell you, tomorrow, at 4:30, you could meet a woman who has been scientifically chosen to be your perfect mate?

00:15:16:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:16:220000.Dialogue: I would snort in derision and throw my arms in the air, exhausted by your constant tomfoolery.

00:15:27:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:27:080000.Dialogue: But we-we put all your vital information into this dating site, answered all their questions just like you would, and they found a match for you. Her name is Amy Farrah Fowler.

00:15:37:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:37:130000.Dialogue: Please. Even assuming you could answer any question the way I would, the algorithms used by matchmaking sites are complete hokum.

00:15:44:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:44:230000.Dialogue: And that's exactly the answer we gave to the question: "What is your attitude towards online dating?"

00:15:48:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:48:210000.Dialogue: Howard wanted to write "mumbo jumbo," but I said no. Our Sheldon would say "hokum."

00:15:58:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:58:110000.Dialogue: Come on, where's your scientific curiosity?

00:16:00:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:00:220000.Dialogue: Well, most of it is being applied to unraveling the secrets of the universe while the rest of it's wondering why I'm having this conversation with you.

00:16:07:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:07:090000.Dialogue: Okay, how about this. Even Spock had a date once every seven years.

00:16:13:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:13:020000.Dialogue: He didn't date. It was pon farr. His blood boiled with mating lust.

00:16:17:210000.Dialogue: Well, why-why don't you start with a cup of coffee, and you can pon farr Amy Farrah Fowler later.

00:16:26:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:26:040000.Dialogue: All right, you can have a hot chocolate.

00:16:28:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:28:030000.Dialogue: As I will not be engaging in this nonsense, my choice of beverage is moot. But for the record, I only drink hot chocolate in months with an "R" in them.

00:16:49:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:49:180000.Dialogue: Sheldon, I've hidden the dirty sock from the roof somewhere in your apartment.

00:16:57:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:57:220000.Dialogue: Unless you are willing to come with us to meet this girl, it will remain there forever.

00:17:06:040000.Speaker: Raj

00:17:56:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:56:180000.Dialogue: Are you out of your mind?!

00:18:02:070000.Scene: The hallway. Leonard is finishing off a bottle of spirits. He opens the lift and drops the bottle inside.
00:18:02:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:02:070000.Dialogue: I'm really starting to think there's a double standard here.

00:18:11:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:11:110000.Dialogue: In a few minutes, when I gloat over the failure of this enterprise, how would you prefer I do it? The standard "I told you so"? The classic "neener-neener"? Or just my normal look of haughty derision?

00:18:25:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:25:100000.Dialogue: You don't know we're wrong yet.

00:18:29:220000.Speaker: Amy
00:18:29:220000.Dialogue: WOMAN: Excuse me. I'm Amy Farrah Fowler. You're Sheldon Cooper.

00:18:33:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:33:170000.Dialogue: Hello, Amy Farrah Fowler. I'm sorry to inform you that you have been taken in by unsupportable mathematics designed to prey on the gullible and the lonely. Additionally, I'm being blackmailed with a hidden dirty sock.

00:18:46:230000.Speaker: Amy
00:18:46:230000.Dialogue: If that was slang, I'm unfamiliar with it.

00:18:51:050000.Speaker: Amy
00:18:51:050000.Dialogue: If it was literal, I share your aversion to soiled hosiery.

00:18:54:210000.Speaker: Amy
00:18:54:210000.Dialogue: In any case, I'm here because my mother and I have agreed that I will date at least once a year.

00:19:00:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:00:160000.Dialogue: Interesting. My mother and I have the same agreement about church.

00:19:05:070000.Speaker: Amy
00:19:05:070000.Dialogue: I don't object to the concept of a deity, but I'm baffled by the notion of one that takes attendance.

00:19:10:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:10:190000.Dialogue: Well, then you might want to avoid East Texas.

00:19:14:130000.Speaker: Amy
00:19:14:130000.Dialogue: Noted. Now, before this goes any further, you should know that all forms of physical contact up to and including coitus are off the table.

00:19:24:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:24:170000.Dialogue: May I buy you a beverage?

00:19:38:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:19:38:070000.Dialogue: Good God, what have we done?
